review_blob: Zythos 2016. Pours in clean amber body with low white head. Aroma has mostly caramel, clean. Taste has medium caramel sweetness with herbal bitterness. Carbonation is full, body full as well.

Zythos 2016. Light hazy pale body with low white head. Aroma has brett character with light litchi citrus touch, mango, well balanced. Taste has high fruity mango, almost strawberry sweetness with light to none bitterness and brett after taste. Body is full, high carbonation. Top 3 beers on Zythos for me.

Zythos 2016. Pours in pale body with medium head. Aroma has citrus upfront, little bit grassy. Taste has higher bitterness with grassy sweetness, lemon, zest, well balanced. Body is full, medium carbonation.
Zythos 2016. Hazy yellow body with high white foam. Aroma has banana character, bubble hum, yeasty. Taste has high grassy character, almost astringent. Body is full, high carbonation.
Zythos 2016. Black body with medium tan head. Aroma has light caramel, light touch of oak, sweet woody notes. Taste has medium sweet oaky character, lightly acidic. Body is full, poor carbonation.

Zythos 2016. Clear amber body with medium head. Aroma has a lot of caramel upfront with characteristic cognar notes, oaky. Taste has cognac sweetness upfront with low to none bitterness. Alcohol touch in the after taste. Body is full, high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in red body with rose medium high head. Aroma has sour character with cherry background. Taste has medium vigenarur cherry taste, low to none bitterness, berries, well balanced,. Body is full, high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in dark amber body with medium head. Aroma is loaded with green apples as the previous blonde, malty sweetness. Taste has medium green apple character, low bitterness. Body is full, medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in hazy pale, little amber body with low head. Aroma has fruity citrus wheat character, coriander tones, malty sweetness. Taste has low earthy bitterness with low malty sweetness, pretty flat compared to the aroma, too bad. Little bit yeasty in the background. Body is low, flat, medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in clear pale body with no head at all. Aroma has alcoholic touch with a lot of green apples character. Taste has medium green apple juice sweetness with medium bitterness. Body is full, high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in hazy yellow amber body with medium frothy head. Aroma has acidic character upfront with tart notes, cheese, little bit grassy and citrus. Taste has strong acidic kick upfront with tart character, citrus, apple, little bit of tropical fruit too. Dry palate. Body is full, high carbonation. Very good.

Bottle. Pours in clear pale body with high white head. Aroma has malty grainy character. Taste has high malty sweetness with medium dough bitterness, off balanced, high on alcohol. Body is full, heavy, medium high carbonation.

Bottle. Dark brown body with low head. Aroma has light brown sugar sweetness, caramel, chcocolate notes. Higher alcohol present. Taste has high chocolate flavour, low earthy bitterness, light cookie notes.  Body is full, medium carbonation.
Bottle.  Hazy golden, light white head. Aroma has malty honey, caramel. Taste has high bitterness, caramel sweetness. Body full, medium carbonation.

On tap, HL. On tap. Hazy amber body with white stable head. Aroma has fruity character, little bit grassy. Taste has high bitterness, grassy with fruity notes, mostly citrus, malty sweetness. Body is full, high carbonation.

On tap, HL. Dark body tan brown bubbly head. Aroma has roasty character, hints of coffee. Taste has strong coffee and roasty character, high sugar sweetness. Body is medium, not creamy high carbonation, sticky. Astringent.

On tap, ML. Pours in hazy yellow body with light white head. Aroma has yeasty character, light spicy. Taste has medium bitterness upfront with malty sweetness dominated mostly by yeasty spice character, hints of honey. Well a pretty neutral saison. Body is full, high carbonation.
beer_name: De la Senne / Thiriez Birthday Session

review_blob: On tap, HL. Pours in hazy body with high creamy white head. Aroma has fruity citrus aroma with honey malty character. Clean character. Taste has medium acidic bitterness, grassy, light fruity touch, odd yeasty touch. Body is medium, flat, medium carbonation. Good lacing.

On tap, ML<,/b> Pours on red body with pink fluffy head. Aroma has gentle raspberry character, little bit acidic on the nose. Taste has high sourness, vinegar background, light raspberry notes. Body is flat, medium, refreshing, medium low carbonation.
On tap, HL. Clear amber body with light white good lancing. Aroma is herbal, caramel, toffee, very herbal. Taste has high bitterness, herbal. Body is medium, high carbonation.

On tap, ML. Pours in red body with pink fluffy head. Aroma has sour character with light sweetness. Taste has sour acidic kick upfront, not much cherries in there, cheese notes, funky. Decent. Body is medium, medium low carbonation.

On tap, moeder lambic. Black body with huge velvet creamy brown head, excellent lacing. Aroma has light roasty sweetness, caramel, toffee, like dark chocolate mousse. Taste is bitter upfront with smooth caramel and toasty sweetness. Cocoa in the background. Velvet body, like swallowing angel wings. Balance behind the words, smooth like a frothy dark chocoolate. Body is medium, low carbonation, smooth texture.

On tap. Pours in hazy yellow body with low head. Aroma has light floral citrus aroma, medium sweetness in the background. Taste has high citrus sweetness upfront, light acidic bite, medium bitterness. Body is full, medium carbonation.
Bottle. Clear pale body with low white head. Aroma has sweet artificial mango which goes into a taste as well, just sweetness with mango character, no bitterness. Body is full, medium carbonation.

On tap, Hoppy Loft. Dark amber body with medium white head. Aroma has light caremel, roasty notes as well as light sour kick. Taste has medium sour acidic sweetness, low to none bitterness, little bit of fruity acidic taste in the background but the palate is pretty flat. Body is full, medium carbonation.

On tap, salon piva. Pours in almost clear amber body with medium white head. Aroma has light stone fruit character upfront, spicy and carames notes, as the beer warms up little bit of diacetyl is present. Taste has medium malty sweetness with earthy medium bitterness balanced, palate is dry, as usual for Albrecht beers, little bit yeasty character in the background. I dont really get much vanilla in this one, even when warmed up. Probably little bit too young still. Body is medium with medium high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in cloudy amber body with medium low white head. Aroma has belgian spiciness, grassy background. Taste has medium earthy bitterness upfront with a yeasty character in the following. Very cloudy, probably end of the barrel as it has a lot of yeast. Body is medium, medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in amber pale body with low white head, poor lacing. Aroma has saison character, little bit acidic in the background, malty. Taste has wheat sweet character upfront with medium low earthy bitterness, spiciness from the yeast, acidic background. Not much kiwi. Body is medium with high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in hazy amber body with medium white head. Aroma has spicy yeast character, characteristic spelt profile, light acidity. Taste has medium spelt sweetness with medium-low bitterness, acidic kick in the background. Body is full, high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in copper light hazy body with medium low white head. Aroma has spicy character, light malty profile. Taste has malty sweetness with low to none bitterness. Flat profile. Body is medium with medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in light hazy pale with medium low stable frothy head. Aroma has spicy character, leaves, herbal. Taste has high spicy sweetness with earthy bitterness. Gentle honey malty sweetness with well balanced spisiness. Body is full, high carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in dark hazy body with no head at all. Aroma is pretty fruity, mostly dark fruits, yeasty, light touch of alcohol, herbal, honey. Taste has very strong dark sugar sweetness, caramel, honey, light bitterness. Body is heavy, medium carbonation, soft.

Bottle. Pours in light hazy amber body with medium white head. Aroma has clean malty profile with hints of caramel. Taste has upfront strong bitterness balanced with intense caramel crisp sweetness, almost burnt. Body is full, medium carbonation.

Salon Piva. Pours in golden pale color with medium white head. Aroma has citrus character, floral, pine. Taste has medium malty support with citrus sweetness, little bit off balanced to sweetness, given as the beer warms up its overly sweetness and hard to finish, thus the lower drinkability. Body is full, medium carbonation.

Salon Piva. Pours in pale red body with almost pink medium head. Aroma has mostly blueberry character with some honey malty notes, really well balanced. Taste has medium malty sweetness, little bit of blueberry but I would welcome little bit more as the appearance and aroma was strong enough. Body is medium with higher carbonation, good drink ability.

Salon Piva. Pours in pale to white hazy body with medium white head and good lacing. Aroma has mild fruity character with spiciness in the background, floral with low herbs notes. Taste has medium malty sweetness with low earthy hops, well balanced. Body is medium, medium-low carbonation.

Salon Piva. Pours in pale body with good stable head. Aroma has malty profile with apple character. At first I thought its an ale but I was told it should be a lager. Taste has medium bitterness, little bit yeasty, fruity. Body is full, medium carbonation.

Salon Piva. Pours in pale to golden body with medium frothy head with solid facing. Aroma has the typical sweet coco soraci character with some honey and as the beer warms up little bit of floral aroma. Taste has medium noble bitterness with low malty background. Notes of acidity in the after taste. Body is medium with medium carbonation as well, highly drinkable.

Salon piva. Pours in dark copper body with no head. Aroma has forest fruits upfront, berries, mostly mulberry, alcoholic. Good but as it warms up the balance is off with little bit of burned rubber. Body is heavy, low carbonation.

Pours in dark amber body with white head. Aroma has yeasty character upfront with caramel following right after, hints of earthy bitterness. Taste has high harsh almost astringent bitterness with the medium caramel sweetness feels like burned caramel. Body is medium to full with high carbonation.

Pours in clear pale, amber body with low to none white head. Aroma has malty sweetness, little bit funky. Taste has high harsh bitterness upfront, low to medium malty sweetness, earthy bitter aftertaste. Body is medium body wit higher carbonation.

PET from the brewery. Pours in hazy yellow body with medium frothy head. Aroma is yeasty, light grainy. Taste has medium malty sweetness, yeasty after taste, low to medium bitterness. Body is full, high carbonation.

PET bottle from the brewery. Pours in clear yellow body with white low head. Aroma has a lot of citrus, grapefruit and orange zest. Taste has high bitterness, citrusy, earthy. High carbonation and medium body, pretty full for such low plato. Good.

On tap, beergeek bar. Pours in golden, almost clear body with medium white head. Aroma has spicy yeast character, clean fermentation malty profile. Taste has sugar sweetness upfront with yeasty character across the palate. Grassy bitterness. Really matches the style, even little too much as Ive expended it to be loaded with new era hops :)
beer_name: emesln pivovar CLOCK / Pivo Falkon Tripel Penetration

review_blob: On tap, JBM. Pours in light hazy golden color with huge white creamy head. Aroma is hoppy citrus aroma upfront, going to the tropical fruits as it warms up, nice balanced. Taste has medium to high bitterness upfront also fruity, little bit of earthy in the after taste. Body is medium-full with medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in black body with low tan head. Aroma has strong roasted coffee character, light peppery with caramel sweetness, well balanced. Taste has high acidic bitterness upfront with long lasting coffee bitter after taste. Body is medium-low, kinda watery. Good.

Can, badflash. Pours in black body with medium-light tan creamy head. Aroma has roasty character, sweet nutty notes, floral, brown sugar, I think I can get a hint of coconut too. Well balanced, woody. Taste has medium bitterness, earthy, caramel sweetness, smooth caramel after taste. Body is full, medium carbonation.

Bottle. Pours in hazy orange-pale body with low white head, poor retention. Aroma has high pine hop character, tropical fruits, tangerine, well balanced. Taste has a lot of dark fruits upfront, tropical fruits in the background, loaded with hop but the bitterness is well balanced with the subtle honey sweetness. Body is full, medium carbonation.
UPDATED: MAR 30, 2016

Bottle. Pours in black body with light tan head. Aroma has light roasty character, high caramel. Taste has high sweetness upfront, mostly caramel and roasty, coffee character. Bitterness is in the background with medium earthy notes. Body is heavy, medium-high carbonation.
